  <title>
    <phrase>Show Sample Points</phrase>
    
  </title>


  <indexterm significance="normal"><primary>Sample Points</primary></indexterm>
  


  <para>
    This command enables and disables showing the sample points in the image
    window. Sample points are used to display color informations of up to four
    pixels in the <link linkend="gimp-sample-point-dialog">sample points
    dialog</link>.
  </para>
  


  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activating the Command</phrase>
      
      
      
      
      
      
    </title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access this command from the image menubar through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>V</accel>iew</guimenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Show Sample Points</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>

        
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
